review_blob: Truly an explosion of hops in a glass. On handpull in the Sheffield Tap, poured into a half pint mini glass. Haze from the dry hopping, they must have used the freshest finest hops here and it shows.
This is just pretty average - quite an old bottle so maybe it was better fresh but for me just fell a bit flat
Incredible smoked beer - mouthfeel is stunning the smoke balance is perfect and it's the essence of balance and class.
ber craft. Hugely over bittered, no aroma really but like being kicked in the teeth by pellet hops. No discernible character beyond the taste of pellets.
Pretty bad - no bottling date so assuming fresh. This is all hop bitterness and dank, nothing to speak of in terms of hops. No real malt character. Craft.
Liked this - malty fusion of different grain flavours. No hop character but solid combination of malt flavours
Totally awesome old ale and not far off fillers va in terms of elegance. Beautiful colour and the aroma's all plums and raisins. Uncredible.
beer_name: Thornbridge / Dark Star Coalition Old Ale

review_blob: Masterful brew - classic Thornbridge: at once both defining and redefining a style. Rich and heady with the honey packing a punch. Not an imperial stout but a clear traditional ale. Not much else to say but this is one of the best english regular beers - file in the same category as VIntage Ale etc.
Average from Mikkeller - tasted nice, but nothing particularly outstanding about it...
Something not quite right here but I can't figure it out. full bodied yes and pale but something weird in the hop character - not oomph ing it for me
Decent but I don't get much Belgian from it - I'd much rather have e.g. Bristol beer factory ultimate stout which does similar bettet
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Belgian Style

review_blob: Tasty but pretty average us style ipa. What to say? Nice hops, nice flavour all the elements in place but nothing zingy for me
No bottling date so I'll assume it's fresh. Aroma is beautiful - all citrus and marmalade. Flavour is disappointing though, overly bitter with not enough support
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Summit

review_blob: Stunning beer - beautiful fruit laden aroma that follows through into the flavour. Almost flawless

Total craft. Goes hop forward and then some but on the way turns away from being a nice balanced beer into something which has too much hop oils to make a sessionable drink. Pleasant enough in a half but I cant see me having more than a half...
Does not age well. No bottling date so hard to know how old this is but has little aroma and the flavours more bitter than anything
Very good impy stout - good balance of roast and bitterness and solid creamy mouthfeel. Really enjoyed it
Old bottle so not much aroma but huge bitter flavour. Love it very much but wish it was fresh
Interesting stuff - it looks like a lager but has a nose like a beer. Not sure it really works but it's actually quite tasty
Reasonable - think it lacked the oomph needed for a low abv stout. Not sure what the lactose adds but pleasant enough
Doesnt do it for me - Im not sure what I expect as an imperial BIPA but I taste Sorachi and that ruins it for me. Flavour is too burnt out for me to get behind it.
This was dissapointing. Potentially an old bottle but zero aroma and just a huge whack of resiny bitterness. In the end not super nice
beer_name: The Kernel Pale Ale Nelson Sauvin

review_blob: Way way better than I remembered - massive hop oils, small malt character but the hops are awesome. Bonkers
Good beer from brewdog alert - fantastic label, tastes a lot stronger than its given abv. Wish they did thus more often
Really liked this - low abv pale with a good whack of bitterness and a solid hop finish
Textbook barley wine for me. Great aroma, chewy mouthfeel. Beautiful stuff - great barley wine
Really sweet for the abv and oily hops ad up to something quite not quite right. Something wrong goes on
Old bottle - not much hop presence and a big alcohol kick. Nice but I kind of expected something more - might be the us to uk thing but I was dissapointed
Bog standard pilsner - nothing much else to say. Well made but I doubt I could distinguish it from stella
Reasonable citra beer - perhaps to oily but I guess thats the point. As a single hop beer it was okay but as a beer its a  bit wrong
Really malty nice beer - no idea if its a good example of the style but I liked it
Old bottle but still tastes great - solid malt presence a powerful hop flavour. Looks awesome too!
Near as dammit perfect barley wine - boozy plummy hoppy taste and really incredible mouthfeel. Stunning beer.
Great beer as usual - solid malty backbone with a dusting of hops. Body is abut thin but apart from that its awesome!
No. Nose is foul, hints of cleaning fluid and unpleasantness. Taste follows this through but it just gets worse and worse. Quite horrid all round.
Should like this but it doesnt quite work in my mind - the hop flavour is muddy and its a little too sweet. Needs more work to be in Halcyon space...
One of my favourite ipas - loads of hop flavour and aroma. Just a great beer
Dissapointing oatmeal stout - mouse is good abs tempting but has a poor mouthfeel and ends up tasting abut too thin for me
Old bottle - not aged well. All hop flavour has dissipated but loads of hop bitterness remains. Quite harsh.
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Amarillo

review_blob: Quite foul - no head danky aroma and oily hop flavour. Clear bottle too - they just didnt think it through...
Super dank standard ipa from kernel - very unbalanced and bitterness is almost overpowering. Almost unpleasant
beer_name: The Kernel India Pale Ale Columbus

review_blob: Tasted of soap to me but otherwise a bit of a malt fest as would be expected. Hard to get excited about this one
Nose is great but the taste has a black hole. Too much roast in with the hops for me and needs some zing to be considered exciting...
beer_name: Fyne Ales West Highland Black IPA

review_blob: Tasty but to me not much like a lager I would know - has much more malt quality to it. Not that thats a bad thing all things told but its a little surprising. Decent but not particularly exciting.

This is okay - one of the weaker twelve stouts of Christmas. Vanillas a tricky one to get right and this one doesnt quite reach the point of being nice. Big woody all in and diesnt have a clear character overall
beer_name: Bristol Beer Factory Vanilla Milk Stout

review_blob: How the hell do they do it? Nailed the style and then some - really beautiful coffee aroma and flavour, backed up with a great stout oomph. I hate them sometimes...
Rebadged as Devonshire Cat Bitter. BBBB of a medium calibre. Nothing exciting and borders on the tedious. Would be low on the list of things I would order again.

Funny tasting but decent IPA from Acorn, on draft at Devonshire Cat, Sheffield. A lot of these Acorn IPAs are starting to taste the same and this is almost the median of them. Decent hop flavour and aroma, solid chewiness but nothing particularly exciting about and perhaps a little too bitter?
This is great - the dark malts really work well with the yeast flavours. Mouthfeel is fantastic and brings everything home. Awesome
Loved this - really crisp and clear beer, with just the right balance of banana and clove. Just beautiful.
